    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "taking a step back... i mean, what does that even mean? it feels like every \"step back\" i take just makes the hole deeper. it's like there's some fundamental math to life where the effort required to exist is always greater than the reward. if the net value is always zero or negative, then why am i even trying to fight the gravity of it all?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
